l periods. Contributors look at material culture, including findings now available from the Mawangdui tomb excavations; consider death in Confucian, Daoist, and Buddhist traditions; and discuss death and the history and philosophy of war.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aDeath. 0aPhilosophy, Chinese. 4aAsian Studies : Asian Religion and Philosophy. 4aAsian Studies : Asian Studies. 4aAsian Studies : Chinese Religion and Philosophy. 4aAsian Studies : Chinese Studies. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Religion. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Eastern / General.2bisacsh1 aAmes, Roger T., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBerkson, Mark, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCsikszentmihalyi, Mark, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGuo, Jue, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIvanhoe, Philip J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIvanhoe, Philip J., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aJiang, Tao, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOlberding, Amy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOlberding, Amy, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aPeng, Guoxiang, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPoo, Mu-chou, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPuett, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWang, Eugene Y., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438435640423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/docume